LAGOS â€“ In a bid to ease the difficulty faced by motorists at the filling stations, the Action Democratic Party (ADP) governorship candidate, Erelu Kemi Elebute-Halle, has given free fuel to motorcyclists in the state. The gesture was made at BOVAS filling station, Ureje in Ado-Ekiti, the state capital. Speaking at the event, the governorship candidate said she was pained by the high cost of petrol and its resultant effects on transportation, goods and services, hence her desire to contribute her quota in easing the difficulty. Elebute-Halle appealed to the Federal Government to find a lasting solution to the suffering of the people. She urged Ekiti people to vote for a credible alternative in the forthcoming Ekiti State gubernatorial election for the betterment of their state. The elated beneficiaries, who could not hide their joy, thanked the governorship candidate for identifying with them at this critical time.